        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 20 at 3:11PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 310 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Lake Luzerne Campground, or near Lake George Village, moving east at
40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Glens Falls, Hudson Falls, Warrensburg, Whitehall, Salem, Lake George
Village, Fort Edward, Corinth, Granville, Hartford, Cambridge,
Greenwich, Comstock, Day Center, Bolton Landing, Glens Falls North,
West Glens Falls, Lake Luzerne Campground, Poultney Village, and
Kings.

This includes Interstate 87 between exits 16 and 23.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
